riation and reinvention of modernista verse and the dynamics of her breakthrough poetics, a poetics that became a model for later women writers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aUruguayan poetryxHistory and criticismx20th centuryxElectronic books. 0aUruguayan poetryxHistory and criticismy20th century. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Literary.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831105379940 cprintz978030016774040uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030018341240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300183412423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300183412/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY